Sec", 'publication_date': 'Tue, 05 May 2026 02:09:01 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@hackfest/116519419366533226', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["If you've been working on something interesting in cybersecurity, this is your moment. We want to hear from practitioners, researchers, and experts who have real stories to tell — whether it's offensive security, hardware hacking, social engineering, AI, or anything in between."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cfp.hackfest.ca']}}, {'title': 'Possible Phishing 🎣  on: ⚠️hxxps[:]//vk[.]com/away[.]php?to=hxxp[:]//aza[.]scia-a-roma[.]it/conferma/web/login[.]php  🧬 Analysis at: https://urldna.io/scan/69f933313b7750000610a4ac #cybersecurity #phishing #infosec #urldna #scam #infosec', 'publication_date': 'Tue, 05 May 2026 02:09:01 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@urldna/116519377921115682', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Possible Phishingon:hxxps[:]//vk[.]com/away[.]php?to=hxxp[:]//aza[.]scia-a-roma[.]it/conferma/web/login[.]phpAnalysis at:https://urldna.io/scan/69f933313b7750000610a4ac#cybersecurity#phishing#infosec#urldna#scam#infosec'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['aza.scia-a-roma.it', 'urldna.io'], 'url': ['https://vk.com/away.php?to=hxxp://aza.scia-a-roma.it/conferma/web/login.php']}}, {'title': 'Call for Papers is now open for BSides Vancouver Island!We’re inviting speakers from across the community to share their ideas, research, and experiences. Whether you’re presenting something new, lessons learned, or insights from the field, we’d love to hear from you.BSides Vancouver Island is built on collaboration and knowledge sharing—your voice is what makes it valuable.Submit your talk here: https://www.bsidesvi.com/cfp#CyberSecurity #Infosec #BSidesVI2026  #CallForPapers', 'publication_date': 'Tue, 05 May 2026 02:09:01 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@BSidesVI/116519345386743432', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['We’re inviting speakers from across the community to share their ideas, research, and experiences. Whether you’re presenting something new, lessons learned, or insights from the field, we’d love to hear from you.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['bsidesvi.com'], 'email-addr': ['BSidesVI@infosec.exchangeCall'], 'url': ['http://www.bsidesvi.com/cfpALTHide#CyberSecurity#Infosec#BSidesVI2026…and', 'https://www.bsidesvi.com/cfpALTHide#CyberSecurity#Infosec#BSidesVI2026…and']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-7791 - Amazon WorkSpaces for Windows Skylight Workspace Config Service Privilege Escalation', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 22:16:20 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-7791', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Improper privilege management in the log rotation mechanism of the Skylight Workspace Config Service in Amazon WorkSpaces for Windows before 2.6.2034.0 allows a local non-admin authenticated user to place arbitrary files into arbitrary locations bypassing file system permission protections, leading to local privilege escalation to SYSTEM.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-7791vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-7791weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'url': ['https://aws.amazon.com/security/security-bulletins/2026-025-aws/'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-7791']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-42238 - Unauthenticated Remote Code Execution via Backup Restore in nginx-ui', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 21:16:32 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-42238', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["Nginx UI is a web user interface for the Nginx web server. Prior to version 2.3.8, nginx-ui exposes a backup restore endpoint (POST /api/restore) that is completely unauthenticated during the first 10 minutes after process startup on any fresh installation. An unauthenticated remote attacker can upload a crafted backup archive that overwrites the application's configuration file (app.ini) and SQLite database. Because the attacker controls the restored app.ini, they can inject an arbitrary OS command into the TestConfigCmd setting. After the application automatically restarts to apply the restored config, a single follow-up request triggers that command as the user running nginx-ui — typically root in Docker deployments. This issue has been patched in version 2.3.8.", 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-42238vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-42238weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'url': ['https://github.com/0xJacky/nginx-ui/releases/tag/v2.3.8', 'https://github.com/0xJacky/nginx-ui/security/advisories/GHSA-4pvg-prr3-9cxr'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-42238', 'GHSA-4PVG-PRR3-9CXR']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-42222 - nginx-ui: Unauthenticated first-boot instance claim via POST /api/install allows remote bootstrap takeover', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 21:16:32 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-42222', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Nginx UI is a web user interface for the Nginx web server. In version 2.3.5, an unauthenticated bootstrap takeover exists in nginx-ui during the initial installation window exposed by POST /api/install. At time of publication no public patches are available.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-42222vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-42222weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['hey@cvefeed.io', 'security-advisories@github.com'], 'url': ['https://github.com/0xJacky/nginx-ui/security/advisories/GHSA-mxqh-q9h6-v8pq'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-42222', 'GHSA-MXQH-Q9H6-V8PQ']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-42221 - nginx-ui: Unauthenticated First-Run Installer Allows Remote Initial Admin Claim', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 21:16:32 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-42221', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Nginx UI is a web user interface for the Nginx web server. From version 2.0.0 to before version 2.3.8, an unauthenticated network attacker can claim the initial administrator account on a fresh nginx-ui instance during the first-run setup window. The public /api/install endpoint is reachable without authentication, and the request-encryption flow only protects payload confidentiality in transit; it does not authenticate who is allowed to perform installation. A remote attacker who reaches the service before the legitimate operator can set the admin email, username, and password, causing permanent initial-instance takeover. This issue has been patched in version 2.3.8.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-42221vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-42221weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'url': ['https://github.com/0xJacky/nginx-ui/releases/tag/v2.3.8', 'https://github.com/0xJacky/nginx-ui/security/advisories/GHSA-h27v-ph7w-m9fp'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-42221', 'GHSA-H27V-PH7W-M9FP']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-41927 - WDR201A WiFi Extender Stack-Based Buffer Overflow via firewall.cgi', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 20:16:19 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-41927', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['WDR201A WiFi Extender (HW V2.1, FW LFMZX28040922V1.02) contains a stack-based buffer overflow vulnerability in the firewall.cgi and makeRequest.cgi binaries that allows unauthenticated attackers to overwrite the saved return address by sending a POST request with a Content-Length header exceeding 512 bytes. Attackers can exploit insufficient length validation in the fgets() call to achieve arbitrary code execution through return-oriented programming or return-to-libc techniques.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-41927vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-41927weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io', 'made-in-china.com'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.made-in-china.com/showroom/yeapook/#:~:text=Established%20in%202015.%2CDistrict%2C%20Shenzhen%2C%20Guangdong%2C%20China', 'http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/wdr201a-wifi-extender-stack-based-buffer-overflow-via-firewall-cgi', 'https://mstreet97.github.io/security-research/iot/vulnerability-disclosure/ai-assisted-research/cybersecurity/cve/2026/05/04/Teaching_the_Machine_Where_to_Look.html', 'https://www.made-in-china.com/showroom/yeapook/#:~:text=Established%20in%202015.%2CDistrict%2C%20Shenzhen%2C%20Guangdong%2C%20China', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/wdr201a-wifi-extender-stack-based-buffer-overflow-via-firewall-cgi'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-41927']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-41926 - WDR201A WiFi Extender OS Command Injection via firewall.cgi', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 20:16:19 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-41926', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['WDR201A WiFi Extender (HW V2.1, FW LFMZX28040922V1.02) contains an OS command injection vulnerability in the firewall.cgi binary across five request handlers that apply insufficient input validation. Attackers can inject arbitrary shell commands through vulnerable parameters like websURLFilter, websHostFilter, portForward, singlePortForward, and ipportFilter using subshell syntax or unfiltered parameters, with payloads persisting in NVRAM and re-executing on every subsequent firewall.cgi request.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-41926vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-41926weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io', 'made-in-china.com'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.made-in-china.com/showroom/yeapook/#:~:text=Established%20in%202015.%2CDistrict%2C%20Shenzhen%2C%20Guangdong%2C%20China', 'http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/wdr201a-wifi-extender-os-command-injection-via-firewall-cgi', 'https://mstreet97.github.io/security-research/iot/vulnerability-disclosure/ai-assisted-research/cybersecurity/cve/2026/05/04/Teaching_the_Machine_Where_to_Look.html', 'https://www.made-in-china.com/showroom/yeapook/#:~:text=Established%20in%202015.%2CDistrict%2C%20Shenzhen%2C%20Guangdong%2C%20China', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/wdr201a-wifi-extender-os-command-injection-via-firewall-cgi'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-41926']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-41925 - WDR201A WiFi Extender OS Command Injection via adm.cgi (reboot_time)', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 20:16:19 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-41925', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["WDR201A WiFi Extender (HW V2.1, FW LFMZX28040922V1.02) contains an OS command injection vulnerability in the adm.cgi binary's reboot_time function that allows unauthenticated remote attackers to execute arbitrary shell commands by injecting malicious input into the reboot_time POST parameter. Attackers can send a crafted request with shell metacharacters in the reboot_time parameter when reboot_enabled=1 to achieve remote code execution.", 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-41925vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-41925weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io', 'made-in-china.com'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.made-in-china.com/showroom/yeapook/#:~:text=Established%20in%202015.%2CDistrict%2C%20Shenzhen%2C%20Guangdong%2C%20China', 'http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/wdr201a-wifi-extender-os-command-injection-via-adm-cgi-reboot-time', 'https://mstreet97.github.io/security-research/iot/vulnerability-disclosure/ai-assisted-research/cybersecurity/cve/2026/05/04/Teaching_the_Machine_Where_to_Look.html', 'https://www.made-in-china.com/showroom/yeapook/#:~:text=Established%20in%202015.%2CDistrict%2C%20Shenzhen%2C%20Guangdong%2C%20China', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/wdr201a-wifi-extender-os-command-injection-via-adm-cgi-reboot-time'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-41925']}}, {'title': 'CISA adds cPanel and Linux Kernel to KEV', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 17:17:11 +0000', 'source': 'https://thecyberthrone.in/2026/05/04/cisa-adds-cpanel-and-linux-kernel-to-kev/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'ipv4-addr': ['11.110.0.97', '11.118.0.63', '11.126.0.54', '11.130.0.1', '11.136.0.5', '11.86.0.41'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-41940', 'CVE-2026-31431']}}, {'title': 'Progress Patches Critical MOVEit Automation Bug Enabling Authentication Bypass', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 16:34:00 +0000', 'source': 'https://thehackernews.com/2026/05/progress-patches-critical-moveit.html', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['MOVEit Automation (formerly Central) is a secure, server-based managed file transfer (MFT) solution used to schedule and automate file movement workflows in enterprise environments without requiring any custom scripts.', 'The vulnerabilities in question areCVE-2026-4670(CVSS score: 9.8), an authentication bypass vulnerability, andCVE-2026-5174(CVSS score: 7.7), an improper input validation vulnerability that could allow privilege escalation.', '"Critical and high vulnerabilities in MOVEit Automation may allow authentication bypass and privilege escalation through the service backend command port interfaces," Progress Softwaresaidin an advisory. "Exploitation may lead to unauthorized access, administrative control, and data exposure."', 'Airbus SecLab researchers Anaïs Gantet, Delphine Gourdou, Quentin Liddell, and Matteo Ricordeau have beencreditedwith discovering and reporting the two vulnerabilities. There are no workarounds that resolve the issues.', "While Progress makes no mention of the flaws being exploited in the wild, it's essential that users apply the fixes as soon as possible for optimal protection, particularly given thatprior flawsinMOVEit Transferhave been exploited by ransomware gangs like Cl0p."], 'observables': {'url': ['https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgY0BC0ZfiOQsJz-LdE3CCEcrNcsKZq2vaQDObdf-k8AWLpHHXBHgdGfcpakC-JN81pT3FXjW4Y3EFV82j-qe6agmPqcjD6HdMi3_lzZVo6fZxjeFSqRvSbtHblSI9HbxvNQYPBV3An3wCWNMp4-9pbEe67Q6n_phgUlzpMgpu3Fz5iBaqHKXMM3DR8zOJJ/s300-e100/maze-1.png', 'https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhoU_5ichoZ6aB79ladsvjQQQW8nQazY3KoJuUucdAQloicujjbRWekcuxrbzgvi1ybo2U0QYdtknElj8mnTNLfCZ0zhk3l6dlI_HAPwp_q1364fCCjhRLwWU0eq6Lx-3GImhE48flog5flkB08kzwaPoG2hl8Lez6mi3vT7YE6L2PnHpMvlqSPT1_3FsJd/s300-e100/maze-2.png', 'https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiJ